news.title: About 750 houses, shops face eviction in Velachery lake in Chennai
news.para: All encroachers have been given time to respond and if the government finds their replies unsatisfactory, they will be evicted, the state water resources department told the National Green Tribunal Southern Zone (NGT SZ).

news.title: CBI arrests Pearls Group's director after his deportation from Fiji
news.para: ​A team of CBI officials had gone to Suva in Fiji to bring Gill after being deported from the archipelago under 'Operation Trishul' and was placed under arrest after landing here, they said.

news.title: Two-year timeline for 50% pending Jaypee projects
news.para: The timeline submitted by the Mumbai-based group proposes to hand over all 24 projects -- 15 are in Noida, eight are near Yamuna Expressway and one is in Agra -- in the next six to 42 months of the plan being approved by NCLT.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board sells 2 BHK for Rs 1 crore in sector 51
news.para: Of 92 commercial leasehold properties on offer, only two got bidders. Both are located in Sector 49B. Each having a reserve price of Rs 43.03 lakh fetched Rs 46.51 lakh.

news.title: Pune citizens clamour for speedy disposal of MahaRERA cases
news.para: A representation was made by citizen groups to chief minister Eknath Shinde and deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis last week.

news.title: NCLT allows Piramal Capital's insolvency plea against Prithvi Residency
news.para: Piramal had filed its application in January 2022, while the developer had defaulted on its dues in March 2019. The company originally owed the funds to Dewan Housing Finance (DHFL), which has been acquired by Piramal in a bankruptcy auction. DHFL had sanctioned a loan of ₹485 crore to Prithvi Residency in 2017.

news.title: Baring PE Asia looks to pick up stake in Shriram Housing Finance
news.para: Shriram Housing Finance had assets under management (AUM) of Rs 7,200 crore at the end of December. Baring PE Asia had previously been among the major contenders to acquire ICICI Home Finance, a deal that didn't materialise.

news.title: WeWork in talks with investors to restructure over $3 billion debt: New York Times
news.para: In February, WeWork forecast weak current-quarter revenue in a sign that its business was feeling the heat of mass layoffs as companies reduce their real estate footprint.

news.title: Irish Life blocks withdrawals from 500 million euro property fund
news.para: A shift to home working has put pressure on the Irish office market, which has experienced a boom in recent years thanks largely to high levels of investment from multinational tech firms.

news.title: Coastal residents await Kerala coastal zone management authority revival
news.para: The 2011 CRZ notification was superseded by a new set of rules in January 2019 and under revised norms it might be perfectly legal to put up new buildings at the same spots because they reduced the requirement of a 'no development' zone by a factor of 10.

news.title: NCLT approves Suraksha group's bid for Jaypee Infratech
news.para: ​The ruling, which also comes nearly two years after the Committee of Creditors (CoC) gave its nod for Suraksha group's offer, will pave the way for the completion of more than 20,000 housing units in various stalled projects of Jaypee Infratech Ltd (JIL) spread across Noida and Greater Noida in the national capital region.

news.title: Udupi city will soon have LED streetlights
news.para: A proposal of the Udupi city municipality to replace conventional streetlights with LEDs at an estimated cost of Rs 24.25 crore through PPP model has been approved by the government, said Udupi MLA K Raghupathi Bhat.

news.title: Gujarat HC issues notices over construction near monument
news.para: A resident of the area, Janaksinh Parmar, filed the PIL claiming that HR Space Con LLP and Param Con Corp LLP have put up buildings within the 100m prohibited and 200m regulated zones.

news.title: Indore civic body resorts to 'naming & shaming' to recover dues
news.para: IMC zone 7 team on Saturday approached a defaulter with ‘Dhol’ (drum) and informed the neighbors and passersby, through ‘Munadi’ (public announcement), about the total dues of around Rs 2.69 lakh as property and other taxes as due against the property owner.

news.title: Ludhiana authorities remove 800 slums established illegally along Old GT Road
news.para: Municipal corporation Rajeev Bhardwaj said the encroachments were removed from over 2km long stretch of green belt area, which was occupied by slum dwellers.
